\textbf{Problem}: What is the value of $\sqrt{1,\!000,\!000} - \sqrt[3]{1,\!000,\!000}$?\newline


\textbf{Manual Solution}: We have   \begin{align*}
\sqrt{1,\!000,\!000} - \sqrt[3]{1,\!000,\!000}&= \sqrt{10^6} - \sqrt[3]{10^6} \\
&= (10^6)^{\frac{1}{2}} - (10^6)^{\frac{1}{3}}\\
&=10^{6\cdot \frac{1}{2}} - 10^{6\cdot \frac{1}{3}} \\
&= 10^3 - 10^2 = 1000-100 =\boxed{900}.
\end{align*}\newline


\textbf{Chatgpt Solution}: Since $1,\!000,\!000=1000^2=1000^{\frac23\cdot3}$, this is a difference of cube roots: \begin{align*}
\sqrt{1,\!000,\!000} - \sqrt[3]{1,\!000,\!000} &= 1000^{\frac12} - 1000^{\frac23} \\
&= 1000^{\frac23}\cdot1000^{-\frac13}-1000^{\frac23}\cdot1000^0 \\
&= 1000^{\frac23} (0 - 1) \\
&= -1000^{\frac23} \\
&= -\sqrt[3]{1,\!000,\!000} \\
&= \boxed{-100}.
\end{align*}\newline
